TITLE: Cuba's rural towns are hit hard with fuel shortages
SUMMARY: Amid weeklong fuel lines and having to cook with charcoal, the lack of fuel and cooking gas is perceived by many Cubans in the island’s countryside as the last straw

TITLE: Pope Francis shows world his health is improving two months after hospitalization for bronchitis
SUMMARY: Almost two months after being hospitalized for bronchitis, Pope Francis thanked the doctors that caught the infection in a conversation with Telemundo. NBC News’ Anne Thompson reports on the Pontiff’s virtual town hall with young people around the world

TITLE: China faces a new Covid wave that could peak at 65 million cases a week
SUMMARY: The country once had some of the harshest Covid restrictions on the planet, but the response from the government and the public is relatively muted this time

TITLE: Will Chinese hacking derail U.S. hopes for a thaw with Beijing?
SUMMARY: Warnings of a new type of Chinese malware come as Commerce Secretary Gina Raimondo met with her Chinese counterpart

TITLE: Passenger opens plane door during flight in South Korea
SUMMARY: Police detained the unidentified person who opened the door minutes before landing, the airline said

TITLE: Pope Francis skipped audiences because of a fever, Vatican says
SUMMARY: Vatican spokesman Matteo Bruni did not provide any further details on the health of the 86-year-old Roman Catholic leader

TITLE: A tree felled in a storm leaves a nation mourning a 'great loss'
SUMMARY: Sierra Leone has been dealt a “great loss,” the country’s leader said Thursday, after its Cotton Tree, which served as a symbol of national freedom, was brought down

TITLE: New British Cycling rules bar transgender women from competing in elite female events
SUMMARY: Trans women, trans men, non-binary individuals and those whose sex was assigned male at birth will be eligible to compete in an "open" category under the new rules

TITLE: Nigerian chef cooks nonstop for 100 hours to set new world record
SUMMARY: Hilda Baci dished up dozens of Nigerian delicacies, from soups to stew and various proteins and, of course, Jollof rice

TITLE: Gimmick or innovation? Self-driving bus starts taking passengers in U.K. trial
SUMMARY: Autonomous buses began serving the streets of the Scottish capital, Edinburgh, on Monday
